  <section class="process-section">
    <h2>Our Tea-Making Process</h2>
    <div class="process-steps">
      <div class="step">
        <h3>1. Plucking</h3>
        <p>Fresh tea leaves are carefully hand-picked from our lush tea gardens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>2. Withering</h3>
        <p>The leaves are spread out to reduce moisture and prepare them for rolling.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>3. Rolling</h3>
        <p>The withered leaves are gently rolled to release natural juices and aroma.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>4. Fermentation</h3>
        <p>The rolled leaves are oxidized to develop flavor and color.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>5. Drying</h3>
        <p>The leaves are dried to lock in the flavor and preserve freshness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>6. Sorting & Packing</h3>
        <p>The dried leaves are sorted by grade and packed for freshness.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

